  "response_text": "Here's a balanced and healthy weekly meal plan that includes a variety of nutrients. You can adjust portion sizes based on your dietary needs and preferences.\n\n### Weekly Healthy Meal Plan\n\n#### **Day 1: Monday**\n- **Breakfast:** Overnight oats with almond milk, chia seeds, sliced banana, and a sprinkle of cinnamon.\n- **Snack:** Greek yogurt with mixed berries.\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa salad with cherry tomatoes, cucumber, feta cheese, and lemon vinaigrette.\n- **Snack:** Baby carrots and hummus.\n- **Dinner:** Grilled salmon with steamed broccoli and sweet potato.\n\n#### **Day 2: Tuesday**\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs with spinach and whole-grain toast.\n- **Snack:** Apple slices with almond butter.\n- **Lunch:** Turkey and avocado wrap in a whole-grain tortilla with mixed greens.\n- **Snack:** A handful of mixed nuts.\n- **Dinner:** Stir-fried tofu with bell peppers, broccoli, and brown rice.\n\n#### **Day 3: Wednesday**\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie with spinach, banana, protein powder, and almond milk.\n- **Snack:** Celery sticks with peanut butter.\n- **Lunch:** Lentil soup with a side of whole-grain bread.\n- **Snack:** Cottage cheese with pineapple.\n- **Dinner:** Baked chicken breast with quinoa and roasted Brussels sprouts.\n\n#### **Day 4: Thursday**\n- **Breakfast:** Chia pudding made with coconut milk topped with mango slices.\n- **Snack:** Hard-boiled eggs.\n- **Lunch:** Mixed greens salad with grilled shrimp, avocado, and a balsamic vinaigrette.\n- **Snack:** Dark chocolate (70% cocoa or higher) with a handful of almonds.\n- **Dinner:** Zucchini noodles with marinara sauce and turkey meatballs.\n\n#### **Day 5: Friday**\n- **Breakfast:** Whole-grain toast with smashed avocado and poached egg.\n- **Snack:** Sliced bell peppers with tzatziki.\n- **Lunch:** Chickpea salad with cucumbers, tomatoes, red onion, and tahini dressing.\n- **Snack:** A pear or an orange.\n- **Dinner:** Grilled steak with asparagus and a side salad.\n\n#### **Day 6: Saturday**\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie bowl topped with granola and fresh fruit.\n- **Snack:** Mixed berry parfait with yogurt and nuts.\n- **Lunch:** Whole-grain pita stuffed with falafel, lettuce, and tzatziki.\n- **Snack:** Rice cakes with cottage cheese and cucumber slices.\n- **Dinner:** Baked cod with lemon, served with quinoa and steamed green beans.\n\n#### **Day 7: Sunday**\n- **Breakfast:** Oatmeal topped with fresh fruit and walnuts.\n- **Snack:** Sliced kiwi or a handful of grapes.\n- **Lunch:** Spinach and feta stuffed chicken breast with a side of roasted vegetables.\n- **Snack:** Air-popped popcorn seasoned with nutritional yeast.\n- **Dinner:** Vegetable stir-fry with brown rice and a side of miso soup.\n\n### Tips:\n- **Hydration:** Aim to drink plenty of water throughout the day. Herbal teas and infused water can also be great options.\n- **Meal Prep:** Consider preparing meals in advance to save time during the week.\n- **Adjustments:** Feel free to swap meals or snacks based on your preferences, dietary restrictions, or seasonal ingredients.\n\nThis meal plan offers a variety of proteins, healthy fats, and carbohydrates, ensuring a balanced diet throughout the week. Enjoy!",
